page.title: 08GLYNDE CRICKET CLUB
page.content: Glynde and Beddingham Cricket Club is situated by Glynde Reach and is opposite the Working Men's Club. There is a Club House where the players can get changed and a Tea House to get things to eat during a match. The cricket club's full name this year is Glynde and Beddingham Cricket Club{ONE {HUNDRED.}The{Under Fourteens}are not very good, but the adult eleven are. The boy's matches are slow paced because they can't hit the ball a long way yet. The name means that{Glynde {and Beddingham} Cricket Club has existed for one hundred years. There are 4 different teams. Our manager lives in Chiddingly. Some of the team do not live in Glynde.
